cked on the bottom row FIRST (before any top row clicks).\nSo the pattern might be:\n- Click on green blocks in a specific order (e.g., column by column, alternating top and bottom)\n- Or click on bottom row first, then top row\nLet me try clicking on all 14 green blocks in column order: bottom-1, top-1, bottom-2, top-2, etc.\nActually, let me first check what happened. The first bottom block (33, 15) was clicked and it disappeared. Now I have 13 green blocks remaining.\nLet me try clicking on the top block in the same column (27, 15) to see if that works.", "kind": "reasoning", "inContext": false}, {"label": "TOOL CALL: python", "content": "<tool_call>\n<function=python>\n<parameter=code>\n# Click on the top block in the same column (27, 15)\naction([{'action': 'MOUSE', 'row': 27, 'col': 15}])\n</parameter>\n</function>\n</tool_call>", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "TOOL RESULT: python", "content": "executed: true\naction_num: 228\nlevel: 2\nscore: 1\nreward: 0.0\nstate: NOT_FINISHED\nvalid_actions:\n  - LEFT\n  - RIGHT\n  - MOUSE\n  - ACTION7\nboard_changed: true\ngameplay_changed: true\nno_impact: false\ndone: false\nlevel_completed: false\ngame_over: false\naction_display: MOUSE(row=27, col=15)\nexecuted_actions:\n  -\n    action: MOUSE(row=27, col=15)\n    animation:\n      num_frames: 5\n      changed: true\n      only_changed: false\n      total_cells_changed: 36\n      cells_changed_per_frame: [27, 24, 9, 1, 0]\n      objects:\n        - top-left (25,13) 5x5, 25 cells, per-frame [16, 24, 9, 1, 0]\nhud_band: rows 63-63\nno_impact_source: band\nrun_elapsed_seconds: 3605.567407198\ntime_remaining_seconds: 4314.432592802", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}], "hasExactModelContext": false, "requestIndexWithinTurn": null, "messageCount": 0}}}